Tony Okafor, Awka Prominent citizens from Anambra State, including a former governor of the state, Dr Chukwuemeka Ezeife, have intervened in the rift between oil magnate, Arthur Eze, and Governor Willie Obiano. The 13-man peace committee inaugurated by the eminent citizens of the state under the aegis of the Anambra State Elders and Stakeholdersâ€™ Forum will also look into the conflict between the Minister of Labour and Employment, Dr Chris Ngige, and Eze. The committee was also mandated to resolve the crisis between the governor and 13 suspended traditional rulers. The forum took the decision after a meeting at Nimo, in the Njikoka Local Government Area of the state, on Tuesday. The National President of the forum and former Justice of the Supreme Court, Justice Anthony Iguh, who spoke to reporters after the meeting, said as stakeholders, they could not afford to keep quiet in the midst of such a distraction. Members of the committee include the retired Chief Judge of Anambra State, Justice G. U. Ononiba as Chairman; and a former Vice-Chancellor, Nnamdi Azikiwe University, Awka, Prof. Pita Ejiofor, as secretary. Other members are Justice Paul Obidigwe and Prof P. N. C. Umeadi, among others. They were mandated to identify the immediate and remote causes of the dispute and submit a report within 30 days. Copyright PUNCH.
